The WhatA gesture recognition and motion tracking palm-bracelet is in the works. But what is that  actually? A palm-bracelet that will not only recognize gestures but will also allow you to use your hands in a Virtual- or Augmented-Reality. Our creation can become whatever you desire in any virtual environment via a series of attachable modules.

 
 The WhoThe team of BrainHUB consists of software developers & engineers, an industrial designer and an economist. Our mission - to develop simple but working solutions to technically challenging problems. We hope that you will share our enthusiasm when you experience your hands at work in a virtual world. We are neither the first nor the only ones trying to come up with such a device like "GR". But we aim to be the ones that ultimately create an elegant solution one. The WhySo why are we doing this exactly? Well, not only, is the problem and its technicalities fascinating, but its solution would also has the potential to revolutionize man's interaction with computer systems. The How Currently, our creation is still only a laboratory prototype. Nonetheless, it is the culmination of seven other preceding versions - each one being a crucial step in the developmental process. We are asking for your support, so that we can take the decisive step of turning our prototype into a product.Whether this happens or not depends on those of you who are devoted to making the future a thing of the present.Another reason to turn to you is because your input on Indiegogo is invaluable to us. Each of our devices is as unique and personal as a your hand: tell us your suggestions and we will gladly comply to any special requests and cool ideas you may have.Let us know what you think on our e-mail: ideas@brainhub.co and you might become part of BrainHUBs history. Let’s walk the creative path together and experience the pure joy of turning an idea into reality. Chalenges & RisksAs with any project in development, ours isn't short on risks and challenges. Our first hurdle was to develop attachable modules for the device which could apply its functionalities to a specific task.. For example: it may be used to control a PC and then, by plugging a VR module, to also act as a gaming controller.The technical challenge at hand is fraught with risks. Namely:
The development process may be lengthy;
Making the device compatible with other systems and devices will also take quite some time;
Turning real-life gestures into mathematical abstractions is a buggy process;
Due to all of the above, the development process will take place on a step-by-step basis.Thankfully, we can overcome these obstacles with your support. Our work will focus on:
Developing a unified design for the bracelet and modules;
Designing an industrial blueprint;
Developing three generations of specialized GR devices;
finalizing first version of our SDK
Those of you that get a perk will gain an exclusive preview of our work. The rest will get an update a week later. FAQWho are the people behind BrainHUB?- Check us out at: https://brainhub.co How long have we been working on the project?- A little over a two years . Is the money going to be enough?- The amount we are asking for will allow us to make a crucial step in the developmental process.What if you fail to reach the funding target?- We would have still benefitted greatly by getting some feedback from you. The work itself would still go on as usual, just slower. Some Indiegogo campaigns promise merch, glam and glory to their supporters. Why are your perks so humble?- Your ideas will be included in the final version of the product. In the end, you will own a device which you partly created. You gotta admit that´s kinda awesome.
